'''The Art of Painting''' is a c. 1666 oil on canvas by the Dutch master [[Johannes Vermeer]]. It depicts an artist at his easel painting a model dressed as Clio, the muse of history, in a Dutch interior hung with a map of the Low Countries.

The work is widely read as an allegory of painting itself and is considered one of Vermeer's most ambitious compositions. It has belonged to the collection of the [[Kunsthistorisches Museum]] in [[Vienna]] since 1946.
